From February 19, 2020 to April 15, 2020, a total of 12870 patients referred to the hospital emergency department, of which 2968 were hospitalized with COVID-19 diagnosis. The mean of age was 55.50 ± 15.15 years and the median of age was 56(46-65) years. The majority of cases were in the age group of 50 to 60 years (Fig. 1
). Also, most cases (66%) were male. The male-to-female ratio was 1.93:1. CFRs are shown in Table 1
. Totally 239 deaths occurred during the entire study period, so the overall CFR was calculated to be 1.85% based on the total number of patients (both outpatient and inpatient) and also CFR was calculated to be 8.06% among hospitalized patients.
